Prepare the Atlas

setwd("R:/Hominid Paleobiology/Projects/Hominoid Faces")

#check that atlas looks right
plotAtlas(atlas)

cebus <- read.pts("Landmarks/fixed landmarks 700k-triangle faces/Cebus_apella_f_cranium_MCZ-31072_v4-decimated25.pts")

Procrustes

setwd("R:/Hominid Paleobiology/Projects/Hominoid Faces")

#Procrustes registration of slid semis, so we can compare to initial output from placePatch

procrustes <- procSym(patched)
## performing Procrustes Fit in...  0.06240082 secs 
## Operation completed in 0.0634009838104248 secs
proccoords3d <- procrustes$rotated

slide_Procrustes <- procSym(slide$dataslide)
## performing Procrustes Fit in...  0.07800102 secs 
## Operation completed in 0.0936009883880615 secs
slide_proccoords3d <- slide_Procrustes$rotated

#extract coordinates of the mean shape
meanshape <- procrustes$mshape
slide_meanshape <- slide_Procrustes$mshape

Viewing 3D in R — library(rgl)

deformGrid3d(meanshape, slide_meanshape)

PCplot <- bindArr(procrustes$rotated, procrustes$mshape, along = 3)
dimnames(PCplot)[[3]] <- c("Cebus", "Gorilla gorilla", "Gorilla beringei", "H. sapiens USNM", "H. sapiens DUKE", "Hylobates", "Macaca", "Nasalis", "Pan troglodytes", "Pan paniscus", "Pongo abelii", "Pongo pygmaeus", "Symphyalangus", "Average")

Plotting Results

PCA with 1st iteration of sliding

setwd("R:/Hominid Paleobiology/Projects/Hominoid Faces")

library(ggplot2)


#visualise Principal Components Analysis for rotated and adjusted landmark+semilandmark coordinates


library(geomorph)
## Loading required package: ape
proccoords2d <- geomorph::two.d.array(as.array(PCplot))

prelimPCA <- prcomp(proccoords2d)

prelimPCAscores <- prelimPCA$x

forPlotPCA <- data.frame(Taxon=dimnames(prelimPCAscores)[[1]],
                      PC1=prelimPCAscores[,1],
                      PC2=prelimPCAscores[,2])

ggplot(forPlotPCA, aes(x=PC1, y=PC2, label=Taxon), show.legend=FALSE)+ geom_point(size=5) + ggtitle("PCA of Procrustes Aligned Hominoid Landmarks and Sliding Semilandmarks (1st Run)") + theme_bw(30) + geom_text(check_overlap = FALSE, nudge_y = -0.009, size=5)

PCA from Sliding Semis (2nd Iteration)

setwd("R:/Hominid Paleobiology/Projects/Hominoid Faces")

slide_PCplot <- bindArr(slide_Procrustes$rotated, slide_Procrustes$mshape, along = 3)
